==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spoonful
<hw>Spoon"ful</hw> <pr>(-f⟦usdot⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Spoonfuls</plw> <pr>(-f⟦usdot⟧lz)</pr>.</plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quantity which a spoon contains, or is able to
contain; <as>as, a tea<ex>spoonful</ex>; a
table<ex>spoonful</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, a small quantity.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spoonily</ent>⟦br⟧
